HEADWORD: Lacerated
<hw>Lac"er*a`ted</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>p. a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>laceratus</ets>,
<ets>p. p.</ets>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Rent; torn; mangled; <as>as, a
<ex>lacerated</ex> wound</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>By each other's fury <qex>lacerate</qex></q>
<rj><qau>Southey.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot. & Zool.)</fld> <def>Jagged, or slashed
irregularly, at the end, or along the edge.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>lacerated</ent>⟦br⟧

